President Obama expressed his condolences to the families and loved ones of those who lost their lives in the earthquake and tsunami in American Samoa. He declared a major disaster for American Samoa and stated that the necessary tools will be provided for a swift and aggressive response. The Federal Emergency Management Agency and the U.S. Coast Guard are in close contact with emergency responders and are fully supporting the deployment of resources. The President also offered assistance to Samoa and the region. He assured that resources will continue to be provided and expressed thoughts and prayers for those who have suffered.